[b]Market Pressure Scale[/b]

[b]What it does[/b]

Splits market activity into two separate oscillators on a 0–100 scale: [b]Setup Pressure[/b] measures how much the market is coiling (ATR/Bollinger compression, proximity to range extremes, relative volume), and [b]Impulse Pressure[/b] measures how much an active move is underway (range expansion, volume, candle body size). A phase label combines both into a single readable state at all times.

[b]Why two components?[/b]

Classic volatility indicators go quiet right when a breakout fires — they cannot detect the impulse. Momentum oscillators do the opposite. This indicator tracks both simultaneously so you can see the full coil-and-release cycle in one panel.

[b]Phases[/b]

[list]
[*][b]Coiling[/b] — Setup above 65, Impulse below 45: market is compressed and near a key level, not moving yet
[*][b]Breakout Watch[/b] — Setup above 55, Impulse between 45 and 70: energy is converting — watch for directional follow-through
[*][b]Impulse Running[/b] — Impulse above 70: a directional move is active
[*][b]Sideways / Quiet[/b] — both below 40: no setup and no impulse
[/list]

[b]Signal Markers[/b]

Small labeled markers appear directly on the oscillator with hover tooltips. Six patterns are tracked:
[list]
[*][b]Coiling ▲[/b] — Setup crosses above 65 with Impulse flat
[*][b]Breakout Watch ℹ[/b] — Impulse starts rising while Setup is still elevated
[*][b]Failed Coil FC[/b] — Setup was high but Impulse never confirmed; breakout stalled
[*][b]Naked Impulse NI[/b] — Impulse running above 70 but Setup has collapsed; late-entry warning
[*][b]Double Peak DP[/b] — both components simultaneously above 65; sharp move typically imminent
[*][b]Dual Fade DF[/b] — both components falling from elevated levels; momentum exhausting
[/list]
Each marker is individually toggleable.

[b]Divergences[/b]

Bullish and bearish divergences are detected on three sources, controlled by a shared master toggle with individual Bull/Bear sub-toggles:
[list]
[*][b]Impulse Pressure[/b] — divergence between price pivots and Impulse Pressure, drawn directly on the oscillator
[*][b]StochRSI K[/b] — same pivot logic applied to the StochRSI K line; divergence lines shown in the oscillator when StochRSI is enabled
[*][b]MFI[/b] — same pivot logic applied to the Money Flow Index; detects when directional volume flow diverges from price
[/list]
Pivot lookback and bar range are configurable and apply to all three sources.

[b]Price-chart markers[/b]

Two types of signals appear directly on the candlestick chart, independently of whether the corresponding oscillator curves are visible:
[list]
[*][b]StochRSI crosses ●[/b] — K/D crossovers in the overbought or oversold zone marked as small colored dots (green below the candle for bullish, red above for bearish). Dot size scales with Setup Pressure so structurally backed setups stand out
[*][b]MFI divergence ◆[/b] — lavender diamond marker when the Money Flow Index diverges from price; visible even when the MFI curve is hidden in the oscillator
[/list]

[b]StochRSI overlay[/b]

The standard StochRSI K and D lines are shown as thin curves in the same panel, providing momentum context on the same 0–100 scale. Divergences and cross markers are individually toggleable sub-features.

[b]MFI overlay[/b]

The Money Flow Index is shown as a thin lavender curve (default off). Unlike StochRSI, MFI incorporates volume direction — it measures whether volume is flowing into up moves or down moves. This makes MFI divergences complementary to StochRSI divergences: when the two disagree, it signals a conflict between price momentum and actual money flow.

[b]Dashboard[/b]

A top-right table shows: current phase (color-coded), Setup and Impulse scores with live direction arrows, directional Bias from a configurable MA cross, and range position (where price sits within the N-bar high/low range).

[b]Bias[/b]

Direction is determined by a fast/slow moving average cross with configurable type (EMA, RMA, SMA, WMA, HMA, JMA) and lengths.

[b]Smoothing[/b]

Both output curves can be smoothed independently with any of six MA types (EMA / RMA / SMA / WMA / HMA / JMA) at a configurable length. JMA Phase and Power are also exposed.

[b]Alerts[/b]
All alerts fire only on confirmed bar close by default (configurable via "Alerts only on bar close" toggle).
[list]
[*][b]Coiling[/b] — high setup pressure, low impulse; market compressing
[*][b]Breakout Watch[/b] — setup pressure elevated, impulse beginning to build
[*][b]Impulse Running[/b] — impulse pressure above 70; move is underway
[*][b]Sideways / Quiet[/b] — both pressures low; no directional conviction
[*][b]Signal: Coiling Start[/b] — coiling phase just detected on this bar
[*][b]Signal: Ignition[/b] — coil has fired into an active impulse
[*][b]Signal: Failed Coil[/b] — coil compressed but impulse did not follow
[*][b]Signal: Naked Impulse[/b] — impulse running without a prior coil setup
[*][b]Signal: Double Peak[/b] — two impulse peaks detected in sequence
[*][b]Signal: Dual Fade[/b] — both pressures fading simultaneously
[/list]

